Design and implement the Effect service layer for the agent system.

## Pattern (matching existing tau services)
```typescript
// Service tag
export class AgentManager extends Context.Tag('AgentManager')<
  AgentManager,
  {
    readonly spawn: (opts: SpawnOptions) => Effect.Effect<AgentId, AgentError>;
    readonly get: (id: AgentId) => Effect.Effect<Agent, AgentNotFound>;
    readonly list: Effect.Effect<AgentInfo[]>;
    readonly shutdown: (id: AgentId) => Effect.Effect<void, AgentNotFound>;
  }
>() {}

// Live implementation
export const AgentManagerLive = Layer.effect(
  AgentManager,
  Effect.gen(function* () {
    const pi = yield* PiAPI;
    const config = yield* AgentConfig;
    const agents = yield* Ref.make(HashMap.empty<AgentId, Agent>());
    // ...
  })
);
```

## Services to Define
- AgentConfig: max_threads, max_depth from settings
- AgentManager: spawn/get/list/remove agents
- AgentControl: spawn/send/wait/close/list operations
- Agent: individual worker state and operations

## Error Types
```typescript
class AgentNotFound extends Data.TaggedError('AgentNotFound')<{ id: AgentId }> {}
class AgentLimitReached extends Data.TaggedError('AgentLimitReached')<{ max: number }> {}
class AgentDepthExceeded extends Data.TaggedError('AgentDepthExceeded')<{ max: number }> {}
class AgentAlreadyShutdown extends Data.TaggedError('AgentAlreadyShutdown')<{ id: AgentId }> {}
```

## State Management
- Use Ref/SubscriptionRef for agent map
- Use SubscriptionRef for agent status (reactive)
- Proper cleanup with Scope

## Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All services defined with Context.Tag pattern
- [ ] Typed errors using Data.TaggedError
- [ ] SubscriptionRef for reactive status updates
- [ ] Layer composition for dependency injection
- [ ] No any types anywhere
- [ ] Proper resource cleanup with Scope/finalizers
- [ ] Effect.gen for all effectful code
- [ ] Match existing tau service patterns
